@node "MENU#0004" "Menu: Project"
 Menu: @{fg shine}Project@{fg text}

Contains actions and settings that involve project operations.
@endnode

@node "MENU#0005" "Menu Item:New"
 Menu:@{fg shine} Project
 @{fg text}Item:@{fg shine} New@{fg text}

 Opens a new project window.  The default "untitled" icon will be loaded.


 @{i}@{u}Notes@{ui}@{uu}

 A new project receives all paths reset to the defaults  set in the paths win  dow .
@{fg back}/@KEYWORDS "Creating a new project window.@"{fg text}
@endnode

@node "MENU#0007" "Menu Item:Open"
 Menu: @{fg shine}Project@{fg text}
 Item: @{fg shine}Open...@{fg text}

 Opens a filerequester to be used to select the icon to load.
 @{fg back}/@KEYWORDS "Opening an existing icon."@{fg text}
@endnode

@node "MENU#0008" "Menu Item:Open New"
 Menu: @{fg shine}Project@{fg text}
 Item: @{fg shine}Open New...@{fg text}

Combines the @{"new" link "MENU#0005"} and @{"open" link "MENU#0007"} functions into one action.
@endnode

@node "MENU#0009" "Menu Item:Restore"
 Menu: @{fg shine}Project@{fg text}
 Item: @{fg shine}Restore@{fg text}
 @{fg back}/@KEYWORDS "Restoring a project to it's original state."@{fg text}
 Reloads the icon information from the time it was last saved.
@endnode

@node "MENU#000A" "Menu Item:Save"
 Menu: @{fg shine}Project@{fg text} 
 Item: @{fg shine}Save@{fg text}
 @{fg back}/@KEYWORDS "Saving the icon."@{fg text}
 Saves the icon using the current filename.


 @{i}@{u}Notes@{ui}@{uu}

 Be careful if the name is untitled. You may end up overwriting your default icon.


 This menu operation ignores the "Always overwrite icons?" setting, and will  always overwrite the icon, unlike @{"save as" link "MENU#000B"}.
@endnode

@node "MENU#000B" "Menu Item:Save As"
 Menu: @{fg shine}Project@{fg text} 
 Item: @{fg shine}Save As...@{fg text}
 @{fg back}/@KEYWORDS "Saving the icon under a new name."@{fg text}
 Saves the icon using a file requester.


 @{i}@{u}Notes@{ui}@{uu}

 If the is an existing icon, the actual operation is affected by the Always Ovewrite Icons? setting.
@endnode

@node "MENU#0006" "Menu Item:Close"
 Menu: @{fg shine}Project@{fg text}
 Item: @{fg shine}Close@{fg text}
 @{fg back}/@KEYWORDS "Closing a project window."@{fg text}
 Closes the current project window. If the window is the last project opened, Iconian will quit.
@endnode

@node "MENU#000C" "Menu Item:Import"
 Menu: @{fg shine}Project@{fg text}
 Item: @{fg shine}Import@{fg text}
 @{fg back}/@KEYWORDS "Importing pointer images."@{fg text}

 Sub: @{fg shine}Pointer Prefs...@{fg text}

 Imports a standard OS3.0 pointer preference file. When running on a custom screen, the pointer colors will also be loaded, starting with register 0. The user defined area will be set to the pointer hotspots.
@endnode

@node "MENU#000E" "Menu Item:Export"
 Menu: @{fg shine}Project@{fg text}
 Item: @{fg shine}Export@{fg text}
 @{fg back}/@KEYWORDS "Exporting icon images as source code."@{fg text}
 Sub: @{fg shine}ASM Source Code...@{fg text}
 Sub: @{fg shine}C Source Code...@{fg text}
 Sub: @{fg shine}E Source Code...@{fg text}

 Saves the icon as a source code file containing one or two Intuition image structu res.
 The file is not complete, and will need some hand editing to be useful.


 Sub: @{fg shine}Chunky Array...@{fg text}

 Similar as other source code, but the image is saved as a series of chunky bytes as opposed to a planar structure.

 @{fg back}/@KEYWORDS "Exporting pointer images."@{fg text}
 Sub: @{fg shine}Pointer Prefs...@{fg text}

 Saves both images as a standard, system usable pointer preference file.
 Both hotspots are taken from the upper-left corner of the user defined area tool.
 Two requesters will appear prompting for the resolution types.
 Please note that not all resolutions are available for all machines.
 The exported files may be used in conjunction with the gadget directory custom ization option.
@endnode

@node "MENU#0013" "Menu Item:Buffer Size"
 Menu: @{fg shine}Project@{fg text}
 Item: @{fg shine}Buffer Size@{fg text}
 @{fg back}/@KEYWORDS "Changing the graphic buffer dimensions."@{fg text}
 Subs: @{fg shine}Width=x@{fg text}  @{i}(multiple entries)@{ui}
       @{fg shine}Height=x@{fg text} @{i}(multiple entries)@{ui}

 Enlarges or reduces the usable buffer size.  This operation is undoable, so use caution.


 Subs: @{fg shine}Width=User@{fg text}
       @{fg shine}Height=User@{fg text}
 @{fg back}/@KEYWORDS "Using user definable buffer sizes."@{fg text}
 Changes the buffer to the user defined buffer sizes. These parameters are available from both the CLI and tooltypes.
@endnode

@node "MENU#001C" "Menu Item:Highlight"
 Menu: @{fg shine}Project@{fg text}
 Item: @{fg shine}Highlight@{fg text}
 @{fg back}/@KEYWORDS "Changing the icon highlight method."@{fg text}
 Subs: @{fg shine}Complement@{fg text}
       @{fg shine}Backfill@{fg text}
       @{fg shine}Image@{fg text}

 Changes the icon highlighting method.  If neccesary, the project window will modify it's shape and size.


 @{i}@{u}Notes@{ui}@{uu}

 Backfill images will not be previewed correctly when selected.


 @{i}@{u}See Also@{ui}@{uu}

 @{"Project windows" link "HIT_PROJ_REG"}
@endnode

@node "MENU#0020" "Menu Item:Icon Type"
 Menu: @{fg shine}Project@{fg text}
 Item: @{fg shine}Icon Type@{fg text}
 @{fg back}/@KEYWORDS "Changing the icon type."@{fg text}
 Subs: @{fg shine}Disk@{fg text}
       @{fg shine}Drawer@{fg text}
       @{fg shine}Tool@{fg text}
       @{fg shine}Project@{fg text}
       @{fg shine}Trashcan@{fg text}
       @{fg shine}Device@{fg text}
       @{fg shine}Kick@{fg text}
       @{fg shine}AppIcon@{fg text}

 Changes the icon type.
 Device, Kickstart, and AppIcon types are really not useful, and are only included to be complete.
 Different icon types affect the icon information window.


 @{i}@{u}See Also@{ui}@{uu}

 Icon information window.
@endnode

@node "MENU#0029" "Menu Item:Save Mode"
 Menu: @{fg shine}Project@{fg text}
 Item: @{fg shine}Save Mode@{fg text}
 @{fg back}/@KEYWORDS "Changing how the icon will be saved."@{fg text}
 Sub: @{fg shine}Strip Planes@{fg text}

 Most effecient way to save an icon.  Only the minimum number of planes will be saved.


 Sub: @{fg shine}Current Depth@{fg text}

 The icon will be stored using the exact number of planes of the screen it was designed on.


 Sub: @{fg shine}Force Eight@{fg text}

 Commodores normal save depth.  This format is only useful for eight color icons, designed on an eight color screen.  (8 is the magic number here.)


 Sub: @{fg shine}Auto Size@{fg text}

 The dimensions of the icon will be automatically based on the icon imagery.


 Sub: @{fg shine}Full Size@{fg text}

 The icon dimensions will be the same as the buffer size.


 Sub: @{fg shine}Custom Size@{fg text}

 The icon size will be taken from the current "normal" image's user defined area.  Use the define area tool to select the dimensions.


 Sub: @{fg shine}NewIcon Standard@{fg text}

 The icon will be saved as a 40x36 rectangle, regardless of the image or buffer size.


 Sub: @{fg shine}Explode Mode@{fg text}

 This special save mode takes advantage of an icon's ability to have an image larger than the gadget structure.
 The gadget size will be taken from the user defined area size.  Use the define area tool for this.
 The image size will be automatically sized according to the visible image size, identical to the auto size method.
 To make the icon bevel box appear correctly, you will need to re-create the righthand and bottom line.  Make the right hand line 4 pixels to right from the user area.  The bottom line is 3 pixels away.
 To use this mode, you'll need some patience and practice.
@endnode

@node "MENU#0030" "Menu Item:Newicons"
 Menu: @{fg shine}Project@{fg text}
 Item: @{fg shine}Newicons@{fg text}
 @{fg back}/@KEYWORDS "Newicon support functions."@{fg text}
 Subs: @{fg shine}Save@{fg text}
       @{fg shine}Save As...@{fg text}

 Saves the current project in Newicon format.  The old style icon is determined by the switches below.


 Sub: @{fg shine}Seperate Palettes?@{fg text}

 When selected, each icon image has it's own palette. The palette is only displayed when the image is the current project.
 This option is only available when Iconian is run on a custom screen.


 Sub: @{fg shine}Mark as Standard@{fg text}

 Selects the current project as the standard (old style) image. The project's beveled box will turn be highlighted to signal this.


 Sub: Dot is Standard

 This signals that the Newicon will not have a standard image.
 This can decrease the file size, but will cause incompatibilities when Newicon is not present, both on the host and other computers.
@endnode

@node "MENU#0036" "Menu Item:Iconify"
 Menu: @{fg shine}Project@{fg text}
 Item: @{fg shine}Iconify@{fg text}

 Places Iconian in an asleep state.


 @{i}@{u}Notes@{ui}@{uu}

 The only way to awaken Iconian is by the appicon. Double clicking will simple awaken Iconian.  Dropping icons on the appicon will awaken Iconian, and the icons will be opened as new projects.

 The ARexx port is only active when Iconian is.  ARexx messages sent while Iconian is asleep will be held until Iconian reawakens.
@endnode

@node "MENU#0037" "Menu Item:About"
 Menu: @{fg shine}Project@{fg text}
 Item: @{fg shine}About@{fg text}

 Simply opens an about window.  The current ARexx port is displayed, along with other copyright and version information.
@endnode

@node "MENU#0038" "Menu Item:Quit"
 Menu: @{fg shine}Project@{fg text}
 Item: @{fg shine}Quit@{fg text}

 Quits if all projects have been saved. Otherwise, confirmation must be made to each modified project.
@endnode

@node "MENU#0038" "Menu Item:Save Mode"
 Menu: Project
 Item: Quit

 Quits if all projects have been saved. Otherwise, confirmation must be made to each modified project.
@endnode

@node "MENU#003A" "Menu Item:Undo"
 Menu: @{fg shine}Edit@{fg text}
 Item: @{fg shine}Undo@{fg text}
 @{fg back}/@KEYWORDS "Undoing graphic operations."@{fg text}
 Moves back in the undo chain one spot.


 @{i}@{u}Notes@{ui}@{uu}

 Any changes made to a buffer will destroy all "redos" from that point on.


 @{i}@{u}See Also@{ui}@{uu}

 @{"Redo" link "MENU#003B"}
 @{"Undo Buffers" link "MENU#0042"}
@endnode

@node "MENU#003B" "Menu Item:Redo"
 Menu: @{fg shine}Edit@{fg text}
 Item: @{fg shine}Redo@{fg text}
 @{fg back}/@KEYWORDS "Redoing graphic operations."@{fg text}
 Moves forward in the undo chain one spot.


 @{i}@{u}Notes@{ui}@{uu}

 Any changes made to a buffer will destroy all "redos" from that point on.


 @{i}@{u}See Also@{ui}@{uu}

 @{"Undo" link "MENU#003A"}
 @{"Undo Buffers" link "MENU#0042"}
@endnode

@node "MENU#003C" "Menu Item:Paste"
 Menu: @{fg shine}Edit@{fg text}
 Item: @{fg shine}Paste@{fg text}

 Loads the any current clipboard image as a datatype.


 @{i}@{u}See Also@{ui}@{uu}

 @{"Load Picture" link "MENU#0049"}
 @{fg back}/@KEYWORDS "Pasting images from the clipboard."@{fg text}
@endnode

@node "MENU#003D" "Menu Item:Cut"
 Menu: @{fg shine}Edit@{fg text}
 Item: @{fg shine}Cut@{fg text}

 Places the current image into the clipboard as an image. The image will then be cleared.
 @{fg back}/@KEYWORDS "Cutting to the clipboard."@{fg text}
@endnode

@node "MENU#003E" "Menu Item:Copy"
 Menu: @{fg shine}Edit@{fg text}
 Item: @{fg shine}Copy@{fg text}

 Places the current image into the clipboard as an image.
 @{fg back}/@KEYWORDS "Copying to the clipboard."@{fg text}
@endnode

@node "MENU#003F" "Menu Item:Erase"
 Menu: @{fg shine}Edit@{fg text}
 Item: @{fg shine}Erase@{fg text}

 Simply erases the current image buffer.
@endnode

@node "MENU#0040" "Menu Item:Exchange"
 Menu: @{fg shine}Edit@{fg text}
 Item: @{fg shine}Exchange@{fg text}

 Swaps the normal and selected buffers.
@endnode

@node "MENU#0041" "Menu Item:Paste from Other"
 Menu: @{fg shine}Edit@{fg text}
 Item: @{fg shine}Paste from Other@{fg text}

 Copies the other image into the current buffer.


 @{i}@{u}Notes@{ui}@{uu}

 This operation is backwards from IconEdit's "Copy to Other".
@endnode

@node "MENU#0042" "Menu Item:Undo Buffers"
 Menu: @{fg shine}Edit@{fg text}
 Item: @{fg shine}Undo Buffers@{fg text}

 Subs: @{fg shine}Goto Oldest@{fg text}
       @{fg shine}Goto Newest@{fg text}

 Similar to undo and redo, but will travel the entire possible distance.


 Subs: @{fg shine}Flush All@{fg text}
       @{fg shine}Flush Current@{fg text}

 Frees the memory occupied by the undo buffers.
 "Flush All" will affect all buffers.
 "Flush Current" will only free the current image's undo buffers.
 These operations are not reversable, so a confimation must be made.


 Sub: @{fg shine}Set Memory Size...@{fg text}

 This sets the total maximum amount of memory the undo buffers will occupy.
 For registered users, this value is basically unlimited.
@endnode

@node "MENU#0049" "Menu Item:Load"
 Menu: @{fg shine}Images@{fg text}
 Item: @{fg shine}Load@{fg text}

 Subs: @{fg shine}Picture...@{fg text}
       @{fg shine}Picture and Palette...@{fg text}

 Loads a datatype into the current buffer, according to the current datatype settings.
 If an area is defined, the image will be best fitted into the area.


 Subs: @{fg shine}Normal Image...@{fg text}
       @{fg shine}Selected Image...@{fg text}
       @{fg shine}Both Images...@{fg text}

 Loads icon images into the buffer.
 Normal and Selected load only one image, into the current buffer.
 Both images loads the normal image into the normal buffer, etc..


 Subs: @{fg shine}Default Images@{fg text}
       @{fg shine}WhatIs Images@{fg text}

 Similar to the above three options, but automatically selects what icon to load from.
 Default are system default icons.
 WhatIs is much better, but only works when the whatis.library is correctly installed.
@endnode

@node "MENU#0051" "Menu Item:Save Picture"
 Menu: @{fg shine}Images@{fg text}
 Item: @{fg shine}Save Picture...@{fg text}

 Saves the current image as an IFF brush file.


 @{i}@{u}Notes@{ui}@{uu}

 No run-length encoding is done.  Rather, a simple zero compression is used.
@endnode

@node "MENU#0052" "Menu Item:Move Image"
 Menu: @{fg shine}Images@{fg text}
 Item: @{fg shine}Move Image@{fg text}

 Sub: @{fg shine}Auto Topleft@{fg text}

 Automatically moves the current image to the upperleft corner.


 Subs: @{fg shine}Up@{fg text}
       @{fg shine}Down@{fg text}
       @{fg shine}Right@{fg text}
       @{fg shine}Left@{fg text}

 Moves the image one pixel in the specified direction.


 @{i}@{u}Notes@{ui}@{uu}

 The keyboard equivalents for these are CTRL+Cursor.
@endnode

@node "MENU#0058" "Menu Item:Flip Image"
 Menu: @{fg shine}Images@{fg text}
 Item: @{fg shine}Flip Image@{fg text}

 Subs: @{fg shine}Quick Horizontal@{fg text}
       @{fg shine}Quick Vertical@{fg text}

 A simple flip, either left to right, or up and down.


 Subs: @{fg shine}Smart Horizontal@{fg text}
       @{fg shine}Smart Vertical@{fg text}

 A better flip routine.  Only the occupied area will be flipped.
@endnode

@node "MENU#005D" "Menu Item:Scale Image"
 Menu: @{fg shine}Images@{fg text}
 Item: @{fg shine}Scale Image@{fg text}

 Subs: @{fg shine}Half Horizontal@{fg text}
       @{fg shine}Half Vertical@{fg text}
       @{fg shine}Half Both@{fg text}

 Halves the image in the specified direction(s).


 Subs: @{fg shine}Double Horizontal@{fg text}
       @{fg shine}Double Vertical@{fg text}
       @{fg shine}Double Both@{fg text}

 Doubles the image in the specified direction(s). @{fg back}/@KEYWORDS "Resizing the image."@{fg text}
@endnode

@node "MENU#0064" "Menu Item:Recolor"
 Menu: @{fg shine}Images@{fg text}
 Item: @{fg shine}Recolor@{fg text}

 Sub: @{fg shine}1.3 to 2.0@{fg text}

 Swaps  colors  1  and  2.   Icons  designed before OS2.0 had white in register 1 and black in register 2. With the introduction with OS2.0, black is now in register 1 and white in register 2.


 Sub: 3@{fg shine} to 8 Planes

 Recolors registers 4 through 7 with the highest 4 colors available.


 Sub: Use 2 Planes

 Remaps the buffer down to the first four colors, relying on the current palette values of each pixel.


 Sub: Recolor Pen2 with Pen1

 Remaps all pixels of color 2 with color 1.


 Sub: Swap Pen1 and Pen2

 Remaps colors 1 and color 2.  Has a near equivalent gadget called r@{"emap." link "GADGET.000.017"} /@KEYWORDS "Recoloring the image." /@KEYWORDS "Remapping pen colors."
@endnode

@node "MENU#0069" "Menu Item:Use Brush"
 Menu: @{fg shine}Brushes@{fg text}
 Item: @{fg shine}Use Brush@{fg text}

 Subs: @{fg shine}Brush 1@{fg text}
       @{fg shine}Brush 2@{fg text}
       @{fg shine}Brush 3@{fg text}
       @{fg shine}Brush 4@{fg text}
       @{fg shine}Brush 5@{fg text}

 Selects the current brush to draw with and operate on.


 @{i}@{u}Notes@{ui}@{uu}

 This menu may consist of graphical representations of the brushes, if the appropriate tooltype/cliswitch is activated. /@KEYWORDS "Selecting a different brush."
@endnode

@node "MENU#006F" "Menu Item:Load Brush"
 Menu: @{fg shine}Brushes@{fg text}
 Item: @{fg shine}Load Brush...@{fg text}

 Loads a datatype into the current brush's buffer.


 @{i}@{u}Notes@{ui}@{uu}

 The maximum brush size is equal to the largest project buffer in use.  Images will be scaled to fit this buffer, if scaling of datatypes is set.

 This operation is affected by the current datatype settings.


 @{i}@{u}See Also@{ui}@{uu}

 @{"Load Picture" link "MENU#0049"} /@KEYWORDS "Loading a brush."
@endnode

@node "MENU#0070" "Menu Item:Save Brush"
 Menu: @{fg shine}Brushes@{fg text}
 Item: @{fg shine}Save Brush...@{fg text}

 Saves the brush as an IFF file.


 @{i}@{u}Notes@{ui}@{uu}

 No compression is used when saving the brush.


 @{i}@{u}See Also@{ui}@{uu}

 @{"Save Picture" link "MENU#0051"} /@KEYWORDS "Saving a brush."
@endnode

@node "MENU#0071" "Menu Item:Enter Text"
 Menu: @{fg shine}Brushes@{fg text}
 Item: @{fg shine}Enter Text...@{fg text}

 Brings up a text requester to enter a string to be used by the Paste text drawing mode.


 @{i}@{u}Notes@{ui}@{uu}

 This operation in not available if ReqTools is not installed. /@KEYWORDS "Changing the paste text string."
@endnode

@node "MENU#0072" "Menu Item:Select Font"
 Menu: @{fg shine}Brushes@{fg text}
 Item: @{fg shine}Select Font@{fg text}

 Use the requester to select the font and style for the paste text drawing tool.


 @{i}@{u}Notes@{ui}@{uu}

 The font name and style will be saved when the window font is snapshotted. /@KEYWORDS "Selecting the text brush font style."
@endnode

@node "MENU#0073" "Menu Item:Text Mode"
 Menu: @{fg shine}Brushes@{fg text}
 Item: @{fg shine}Text Mode@{fg text}

 Subs: @{fg shine}Jam1@{fg text}
       @{fg shine}Jam2@{fg text}
       @{fg shine}Complement@{fg text}
       @{fg shine}Inverse Video@{fg text}

 Selects how the text will appear when drawn into the buffer. /@KEYWORDS "Changing the brush text mode."
@endnode

@node "MENU#0078" "Menu Item:Flip Brush"
 Menu: Brushes
 Item: Flip Brush

 Subs: Horizontal
       Vertical

 Flips the brush in the specified direction.
@endnode

@node "MENU#007B" "Menu Item:Scale Brush"
 Menu: Brushes
 Item: Scale Brush

 Subs: Half Horizontal
       Half Vertical
       Half Both
       Double Horizontal
       Double Vertical
       Double Both

 Scales the brush in the specified direction(s).
@endnode

@node "MENU#0082" "Menu Item:Brush Mode"
 Menu: Brushes
 Item: Brush Mode

 Changes the brush mode to one of the following:

 Sub: Matte

 Color 0 will be transparent.


 Sub: Color

 All colors other than 0 will appear in the current pen number.


 Sub: Replace

 Brush will appear exactly as is.


 Sub: Complement

 Brush will XOR (Complement) into the buffer.


 Sub: Smooth

 Colors will be smoothed where the brush holds a color other than 0.
@endnode

@node "MENU#0088" "Menu Item:Handle Position"
 Menu: @{fg shine}Brushes@{fg text}
 Item: @{fg shine}Handle Position@{fg text}

 Subs: @{fg shine}Center@{fg text}
       @{fg shine}Top Left@{fg text}
       @{fg shine}Top Right@{fg text}
      @{fg shine} Bottom Left@{fg text}
       @{fg shine}Bottom Right@{fg text}
       @{fg shine}Custom@{fg text}

 Changes where the "handle" of the brush is.


 @{i}@{u}Notes@{ui}@{uu}

 @{i}Custom@{ui} is meant for future expansion.
@endnode

@node "MENU#0090" "Menu Item:Drawing Mode"
 Menu: @{fg shine}Paint@{fg text}
