@node "HIT_MAG" "Magnification Area"
 Magnification area

 The magnification area is used to edit icon images. To take full advantage of Iconian 3, you must learn how to use and exploit the magnification area.

 Along the right and bottom sides are two scrollers. These control where in the icon image you are viewing.  The position and size of these scrollers are affected by several factors. Magnification level, icon  buffer size, magnification view size, and the current focal point.

 On the extreme right side is the magnification level. When this slider is at the far bottom, the magnification window will display the current proje ct's image at real size. When this slider is at the top, every real pixel will be displayed as a 16x16 box.

 When the pointer is within the magnification drawing area, it will change to one of several shapes. These shapes reflect the current drawing mode. The current position will also be reflected by either a dot or crosshairs following the pointer.

 Each drawing mode has it's own method of operation. Clicking in the magnification area will begin the current drawing mode. Releasing the mouse button will usually finish the draw procedure. The magnification area will update what the finished draw procedure will look like in real time.


 See Also

 @{"Beveled box gadget" link "GADGET.000.03D"}
 @{"Dither type gadget" link "GADGET.000.03C"}
 @{"Keyboard commands" link "KEYBOARD"}
 @{"Magnification level" link "GADGET.000.005"}
 @{"Redo button" link "GADGET.000.00A"}
 @{"Select drawing tool" link "GADGET.000.006"}
 @{"Select pen color" link "GADGET.000.007"}
 @{"Undo button" link "GADGET.000.009"}
@endnode

@node "HIT_REG_PROJ" "Using Project Windows"
Mouse operation in project windows.

 There will be one or two boxes in the window, depending upon the highlight method.  Clicking in either box will select that icon and image as the "focas" project.

 Also, pressing the mouse button in the first box will display what the icon will appear as when highlighted.

 Special operations rely on the center on select setting.


 Notes

 Backfill highlighting preview is unsupported. Instead, the icon will appear complemented when selected.
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.001" "Horizontal scroller"
Slides the view to the left and to the right.
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.003" "Vertical scroller"
Slides the view up and down.
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.005" "Magnification level"
Adjust the magnification level.

Keyboard commands: "<" ">" - Changes magnification level.
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.006" "Select drawing tool"
Changes the current drawing mode.

See Also: Plot       Draw Line Beveled Box Rectangle Filled Rectangle Oval Filled    Oval Fill Filled Polygon Air Brush Define Area Cut Brush Paste Brush Stretch Brush  Paste Text
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.007" "Select pen color"
Selects the color to draw with.
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.008" "Select background color"
Selects the color to erase with.
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.009" "Undo button"
Undos the previous drawing action.

Keyboard command: "u"
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.00A" "Redo button"
Redos the next drawing action.

Keyboard command: "shift-u"
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.00B" "Icon type"
Selects the icon type.

See Also: Menu Item:Icon Type
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.00C" "Highlight type"
Selects the icon highlight method.

See Also: Menu Item:Highlight
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.00D" "Icon left edge"
Changes where the left edge of the icon will be.
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.00E" "Icon top edge"
Changes where the top edge of the icon will be.
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.00F" "Icon stack size"
Changes the stack size of the icon.
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.010" "Free icon position"
Changes the freedom state of the icon.
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.011" "Icon window left edge"
Changes the drawer window left edge.
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.012" "Icon window top edge"
Changes the drawer window top edge.
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.013" "Icon window width"
Changes the drawer window width.
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.014" "Icon window height"
Changes the drawer window height.
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.015" "Center datatype image"
Determines if the image will be centered in the defined area.
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.016" "Integer scale"
Integer scaling will be used.  This helps eliminate artifacts.
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.017" "Remap"
Remapping will be done.
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.018" "Use aspect"
Scaling will retain aspects.
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.019" "Aspect X"
The screen ratio, determined by X:Y.
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.01A" "Aspect Y"
The screen ratio, determined by X:Y.
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.01B" "Scale"
Scales the image to fit inside the defined area or the image buffer.
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.01C" "Stretch"
Image will be stretched to exactly fit the defined area.
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.01D" "Dither"
Dithering will be used.
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.01E" "Clear"
The buffer will be cleared before renderng.
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.01F" "Default icon directory"
Determines where the default icon directory is.
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.020" "Default icon directory selector"
Brings up a directory selector.  Select the default icon directory.

See Also: Default icon directory
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.021" "Default icon image directory"
Determines where the default icon image directory is.
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.022" "Default icon image directory selector"
Brings up a directory selector.  Select the default icon image directory.
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.023" "Default picture directory"
Determines where the default picture directory is.
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.024" "Default picture directory selector"
Brings up a directory selector.  Select the default picture directory.
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.025" "Gadget directory"
Determines where the user gadget directory is. Tool gadget images, user palette, and mouse pointer images will be used if present.

To create tool gadget images, save the images as icons to the gadget directory.  The images are named "Gadget-00" through "Gadget-15". These are numbered from the upper left to lower right.

To change the mouse pointer images, use the "Export...Pointer Prefs" menu item. The pointer files are system 3.0 compatible and may also be edited with the system pointer prefs program. Iconian utilizes the busy image when the select button is pressed.

To specify a palette for custom screen,  save a palette file as "Default.pal" in the gadget directory.  This file will be loaded upon startup. (May NOT be implemented yet)

It is possible to leave out one or any of the above. Iconian will default back to internal images if need be.

See Also:  Export  Palette
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.026" "Use gadget directory"
Determines if the user gadget directory is scanned at startup.

See Also: Gadget directory
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.027" "Gadget directory selector"
Brings up a directory selector.  Select the default gadget directory.

See Also: Gadget directory
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.028" "Default appicon"
Determines what the appicon will be.
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.029" "Default appicon selector"
Brings up a directory selector.  Select the default appicon file.

See Also: Default appicon
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.02B" "Red component value (string)"
Changes the current pen color's red value.
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.02C" "Green component value (string)"
Changes the current pen color's green value.
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.02D" "Blue component value (string)"
Changes the current pen color's blue value.
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.02E" "Red component value (slider)"
Changes the current pen color's red value.
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.02F" "Green component value (slider)"
Changes the current pen color's green value.
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.030" "Blue component value (slider)"
Changes the current pen color's blue value.
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.031" "Copy color"
Copies the current color to the next selected color. The destination color may be selected by picking one from the palette window, or by clicking in the drawing area.  To cancel, select the gadget a second time.

Notes:  This operation currently cannot be undone, so use caution.
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.032" "Exchange color"
Exchanges the current color with the next selected color.  The destination color may be selected by picking one from the palette window, or by clicking in the drawing area.  To cancel, select the gadget a second time.

Notes:  This operation currently cannot be undone, so use caution.
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.033" "Spread color"
Spreads the current color to the next selected color. The destination color may be selected by picking one from the palette window, or by clicking in the drawing area.  To cancel, select the gadget a second time.

Notes:  This operation currently cannot be undone, so use caution.
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.034" "Remap color"
Remaps the current color with the next selected color. The destination color may be selected by picking one from the palette window, or by clicking in the drawing area.  To cancel, select the gadget a second time.
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.035" "Dither method"
Selects the dithering method.
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.036" "Quantize method"
Selects the color reduction method.
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.037" "Palette"
Selects the current pen color.
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.038" "Tooltypes"
Lists the tooltypes of the current icon.
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.039" "Tooltype entry"
Edits the currently selected tooltype.
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.03A" "Add tooltype"
Adds a blank tooltype to the tooltype list.
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.03B" "Remove tooltype"
Removes the currently selected tooltype.

Notes:  This operation currently cannot be undone, so use caution.
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.03C" "Dither type gadget"
Selects the dithering draw mode.
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.03D" "Beveled box gadget"
Selects the type of beveled box.
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.03E" "Macro #1 selector"
Selects macro #1.
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.03F" "Macro #2 selector"
Selects macro #2.
@endnode

