Selects macro #5.
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.043" "Macro #6 selector"
Selects macro #6.
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.044" "Macro #7 selector"
Selects macro #7.
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.045" "Macro #8 selector"
Selects macro #8.
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.046" "Macro #9 selector"
Selects macro #9.
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.047" "Macro #10 selector"
Selects macro #10.
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.048" "Macro #1 string entry"
Specifies macro #1.
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.049" "Macro #2 string entry"
Specifies macro #2.
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.04A" "Macro #3 string entry"
Specifies macro #3.
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.04B" "Macro #4 string entry"
Specifies macro #4.
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.04C" "Macro #5 string entry"
Specifies macro #5.
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.04D" "Macro #6 string entry"
Specifies macro #6.
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.04E" "Macro #7 string entry"
Specifies macro #7.
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.04F" "Macro #8 string entry"
Specifies macro #8.
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.050" "Macro #9 string entry"
Specifies macro #9.
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.051" "Macro #10 string entry"
Specifies macro #10.
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.053" "Auto englarge"
Always enlarges buffer to fit oversized icons.
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.054" "Always overwrite icons"
Existing icons will always be overwritten.
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.055" "Filter datatypes"
Only datatype pictures will be displayed in picture file requesters.
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.056" "Mini sunmouse"
The main window will be activated when the mouse pointer passes over it. This helps for right mouse button drawing operations.
@endnode

@node "GADGET.000.057" "Center on select"
The magnified view will center when the pointer is clicked in the project windows.
@endnode

@node "Gadget.010.000" "Size Window Gadget"
  @{u}Size Window Gadget@{ub}@{uu}

  Sizes the window.  Click and hold the mouse button. Move the window to the desired size and release the button.
@endnode

@node "Gadget.020.000" "Drag Window Gadget"
  @{u}Drag Window Gadget@{ub}@{uu}

  Moves the window.  Click and hold the mouse button. Move the window to the desired position and release the button.
@endnode

@node "Gadget.040.000" "Window Depth Gadget"
  @{u}Window Depth Gadget@{ub}@{uu}

  Changes the window's depth position.  If it is the top-most window, it will be moved to the very back. Otherwise, the window will be moved to the very front.

NOTES:
  Iconian 3 does not support saving window depth positions to preference files. Windows will always be opened in a specific order.
@endnode

@node "Gadget.060.000" "Zip Window Gadget"
  @{u}Zip Window Gadget@{ub}@{uu}

  Zips the window size to the alternate position and dimensions.

NOTES:
  Iconian 3 does not support saving alternate positions to preference files. Only the current position and dimensions will be remembered.
@endnode

@node "Gadget.080.000" "Close Window Gadget"
 Close Window Gadget

 Closes the window.

 @{i}Main Window@{ui}
 Quits the program.  Requesters will appear for any unsaved projects.

 @{i} Project Window@{ui}
 Closes the project.  You must confirm the action if the project has been changed.  If the window is the last open project, the program will quit.

 @{i} Preference and Settings Windows.@{ui}
 Hides the window.  You can bring it back using Windows->Open->* menu items.
@endnode


